# proof402

> x402/HTTP 402 payment middleware for FastAPI and Flask/WSGI.  
> Gate any API behind RLUSD micropayments on XRP Ledger via [402Proof](https://four02proof.onrender.com).  
> Sub-millisecond local HMAC verification. Zero API keys. Zero custody.

[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/proof402)](https://pypi.org/project/proof402/)
[![license](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green)](LICENSE)
[![python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9%2B-blue)]()

---

## Install

```bash
pip install proof402
```

---

## How It Works

1. Agent hits your protected route → middleware checks for `X-Payment-Token` header
2. No token (or invalid) → middleware returns `HTTP 402` + invoice (pay_to, memo_hex, amount)
3. Agent sends RLUSD on XRPL → calls `POST /v1/verify` on 402Proof → receives signed token
4. Agent retries with `X-Payment-Token: <token>` → verified locally in <1ms → access granted

Token verification is pure HMAC-SHA256 — **zero network call, sub-millisecond** when `token_secret` is set.

---

## FastAPI

```python
import os
from fastapi import FastAPI, Depends
from proof402 import Proof402

app = FastAPI()

proof = Proof402(
    endpoint_id=os.environ["PROOF402_ENDPOINT_ID"],
    server_url="https://four02proof.onrender.com",
    token_secret=os.environ.get("PROOF402_TOKEN_SECRET"),  # enables zero-latency local verify
)

@app.get("/api/premium/council")
async def council_verdict(symbol: str, verified=Depends(proof.require_payment())):
    return {"symbol": symbol, "verdict": "BULLISH", "verified": verified}
```

## Flask / WSGI

```python
import os
from flask import Flask
from proof402 import Proof402Middleware

app = Flask(__name__)

app.wsgi_app = Proof402Middleware(
    app.wsgi_app,
    endpoint_id=os.environ["PROOF402_ENDPOINT_ID"],
    server_url="https://four02proof.onrender.com",
    protected_paths=["/api/premium", "/api/council"],
    token_secret=os.environ.get("PROOF402_TOKEN_SECRET"),
)

@app.route("/api/premium/data")
def premium_data():
    return {"data": "paid content"}
```

---

## HTTP 402 Response Format

When payment is required, clients receive `HTTP 402` with:

```json
{
  "error": "Payment Required",
  "invoice": {
    "invoice_id": "inv_abc123",
    "pay_to": "rGATEWAY...",
    "memo_hex": "696e765f616263313233",
    "amount": "0.10",
    "asset": "RLUSD",
    "expires_at": 1747616400
  },
  "instructions": {
    "step1": "Send 0.10 RLUSD on XRPL to rGATEWAY...",
    "step2": "Include MemoData: 696e765f... in your XRPL payment",
    "step3": "POST https://four02proof.onrender.com/v1/verify with invoice_id, tx_hash, agent_wallet",
    "step4": "Retry with header: X-Payment-Token: <token>"
  }
}
```

---

## Options

### `Proof402(endpoint_id, server_url, token_secret=None)`

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `endpoint_id` | str | yes | UUID from 402Proof merchant dashboard |
| `server_url` | str | no | 402Proof server URL (default: `https://four02proof.onrender.com`) |
| `token_secret` | str | recommended | Same `TOKEN_SECRET` as your 402Proof server. Enables zero-network local verification. |

### `Proof402Middleware(app, endpoint_id, server_url, protected_paths, token_secret=None)`

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `app` | WSGI app | yes | Your Flask/Django WSGI app |
| `protected_paths` | list[str] | no | Path prefixes to protect (default: `["/"]`) |

---

## Environment Variables

```bash
PROOF402_ENDPOINT_ID=your-endpoint-uuid
PROOF402_TOKEN_SECRET=your-token-secret   # from 402Proof server env
```

---

## Register Your Endpoint

1. Go to [four02proof.onrender.com](https://four02proof.onrender.com)
2. Register as a merchant → create an endpoint → copy the UUID
3. Set `PROOF402_ENDPOINT_ID` in your environment
4. Set `PROOF402_TOKEN_SECRET` to the same value as your 402Proof `TOKEN_SECRET`

